comment.commentLine: Q1 : As part of the deployment, Oracle always installs the latest Exadata Storage software. This means that different machines could have different versions of the Storage software even if they are deployed around the same time. An example of the difference between machines would be the Kernel version that is installed. Please review the Exadata Storage software version to be deployed with the Engineer during the planning phase of the deployment. Note for VM's UEK2 and UEK4 can not be mixed. Dom0 needs to be equal or higher than DomU. Please indicate desired OS image.
Q2 : If you are using 10G Optical, do you have existing certified SFP Modules that you can use? if not, when do you plan to order them?
Q3 : Will this machine be multi-racked connected over infiniband to another engineered system? If so, please indicate additional machines.
Q3a: If this machine is multi-racked, have you ensured that the InfiniBand IPs do not overlap and that they are in the proper subnet?
Q3b: If this machine is multi-racked, is an InfiniBand Listener needed for SQL communication on the InfiniBand fabric?
Q4 : If requesting LACP, will bond options be different than default? If so, please specify the bond options.
Q5 : Have you ensured that the private IB subnet does not overlap the other networks (client, mgmt, backup)?
Q6 : If this a DR machine, have you ensured the RDBMS version matches the
Q7 : For a rack upgrade/expansion, should the ASM diskgroups be extended or new
Q8: Will the database nodes use LDAP servers for hostname or IP resolution or
User security? If so, have you confirmed the UID/GID's are matching?
Q9: "Will Spanning Tree Protocol need to be disabled on the uplink port?"
